						<summary>
							<p>Copy of a palm-leaf order. Grant of money <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>paṇam</foreign></supplied> by the <foreign>tēvaraṭiyār</foreign> Nāṟpatteṇṇāyira-Naṅkai to the temple for the benefit of mendicants <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kōvaṇavar</foreign></supplied>, <unclear cert="low">devotees of Vīrabhadra</unclear> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vīrapattirar</foreign></supplied> and temple trustees <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tāṉattar</foreign></supplied>. In return, she was appointed to perform several services, including flashing the sacred fly-whisk <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiruveṇcāmarai</foreign></supplied>, the sacred mirror <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tirukkaṇṇāṭi</foreign></supplied> singing holy songs <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiruppāṭṭu</foreign></supplied> while gesturing with her hands <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaikāṭṭa</foreign></supplied>, as well as certain land rights <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>urimai kuṭi</foreign></supplied> </p>						
				</summary>
			</msContents>
			<physDesc>
				<handDesc>
					<p>According to ARIE, it is dated to the 14th century on palaeographical grounds.</p>
				</handDesc>
			</physDesc>
